{"name":"Saint George the Dragon Slayer - Ally","type":"npc","img":"icons/weapons/swords/sword-guard-bronze.webp","system":{"npcType":"dark_presence","oppositionLevel":5,"isMainNPC":true,"biography":"Saint George the Dragon Slayer is a legendary holy knight who wanders Broken Europe hunting monsters and Dark Presences. His story is tragic: as a child, George befriended a young Dragon in the mountains. Years later, when plague struck his village, George begged the Dragon to help save his people. The Dragon, bound by ancient laws forbidding interference in human affairs, refused. George watched helplessly as his family and neighbors died. Consumed by grief and rage at this perceived betrayal, George dedicated his life to becoming a holy knight. He trained relentlessly, mastering combat and learning to resist magic. When ready, he returned and executed the Dragon who had once been his friend. The Church canonized him as Saint George the Dragon Slayer, but the weight of killing his childhood friend left deep scars on his soul. What George doesn't know is that his entire story was orchestrated by the One Who Plots in the Shadows, who twisted a tale of friendship into one of betrayal and violence. Now Saint George can appear as either ally or opponent to the Hunters, depending on their actions. As an ally, he fights alongside them against genuine threats while carefully observing their moral choices. He accumulates Judgment Tokens when Hunters use Dark Ego or magic for good deeds—when enough Tokens accumulate, he admits he was wrong and becomes a permanent ally.","attributes":{"soma":{"current":4,"max":4},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":4,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am a legendary dragon slayer and holy knight of the Church","I hunt monsters and Dark Presences to protect humanity","The memory of my Dragon friend haunts me","I watch to determine if Hunters are heroes or monsters"],"gifts":[{"name":"The Holy Dragon Slayer","description":"Saint George wields a blessed sword that once slew his Dragon friend. When fighting against creatures with monstrous, magical, or supernatural Descriptors, Saint George can spend 1 Fervor Token to inflict 1 additional Wound beyond normal damage, or 1 Wound even if the target succeeds on their Defense Check. The only way to avoid this Wound is to have an Outcome with Increment and spend it to nullify the Gift's effect. Saint George regenerates Fervor Tokens equal to the number of Hunters at the beginning of each Scenario when acting as an ally."},{"name":"The Judgment of the Saint","description":"Saint George keeps everyone under observation, even when fighting alongside the Hunters. During a Scene, if a Hunter activates their Dark Ego to perform a good deed, or uses any Gift that allows them to use magic or manipulate ordinary people to do good in Saint George's presence, he adds 1 Judgment Token to this Gift. Judgment Tokens carry over between Scenarios. When Judgment Tokens equal twice the number of Hunters, Saint George makes amends, declaring he was wrong in his judgment, and puts an end to any Witch Hunt, becoming a permanent ally. Examples: Using Dark Ego to save innocent lives, employing magic to heal/protect the helpless, manipulating nobles to bring justice, sacrificing personal gain to help others."}],"conditions":[],"agenda":["Eliminate Broken Tales that threaten innocent people","Determine if the Hunters are truly heroes or simply monsters","Protect humanity from supernatural threats","Find redemption for killing my childhood friend"],"notes":"Saint George is a RECURRING campaign element who can transition between ally and opponent based on Hunter actions. Track Fervor Tokens (combat resource) and Judgment Tokens (redemption mechanic) secretly. He can appear in multiple scenarios, building tension over time. If Hunters discover his manipulated past and appeal to his Dragon friend's memory, reduce OL by 1 for that Scene as his resolve wavers. Connection to One Who Plots in the Shadows makes him a bridge to discovering the true enemy. Voice: Noble and commanding, but with underlying sadness. Mannerisms: Touches his sword hilt when troubled, distant gaze."},"_id":"ef22a7c6259ddaf2"}
{"name":"Saint George the Dragon Slayer - Opponent","type":"npc","img":"icons/weapons/swords/sword-winged-red.webp","system":{"npcType":"dark_presence","oppositionLevel":5,"isMainNPC":true,"biography":"When Saint George becomes convinced the Hunters are no better than the monsters they hunt, he transitions from ally to opponent, initiating a Witch Hunt to eliminate them. This transformation occurs when Suspicion Tokens equal twice the number of Hunters—accumulated when Hunters use Dark Ego for selfish purposes, harm innocents, or demonstrate monstrous behavior in his presence. As an opponent, Saint George is relentless and terrifying. He publicly confronts the Hunters, accusing them of crimes, reveals evidence he's been gathering of their misdeeds, and gives them one chance to surrender and face judgment. When they refuse, he summons his Paladins (a number equal to the Hunters) and the Witch Hunt begins. During the Witch Hunt, Saint George appears at the worst possible moments—turning allies against the Hunters, disrupting investigations, forcing them to constantly look over their shoulders. His Gift allows him to not only deal devastating wounds but also to nullify actions by Hunters with magical or monstrous Descriptors. He regenerates Fervor Tokens each Scenario, making him a persistent and increasingly dangerous threat. The only way to end the Witch Hunt is to accumulate Judgment Tokens by proving through actions that the Hunters use their powers for good, or to defeat Saint George in combat and reveal the truth about his manipulated past.","attributes":{"soma":{"current":4,"max":4},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":4,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am the Dragon Slayer, and I have seen the truth","These so-called Hunters are monsters wearing human skin","They must be eliminated before they corrupt more innocents","The Church and humanity must be protected from corrupted agents"],"gifts":[{"name":"Witch Hunt","description":"When he becomes an Opponent Dark Presence, Saint George acquires Fervor Tokens equal to the number of Hunters. When facing a Hunter he's been tracking down, he can spend 1 Fervor Token to inflict 1 additional Wound on top of normal damage, or just 1 Wound if the Hunter succeeds on their Defense Check. The only way to avoid this Wound is to have an Outcome with Increment and spend it to nullify the Gift's effect. Saint George can also spend 1 Fervor Token to transform any Position Check's result for an action against him into a Failure, so long as the Hunter performing it has at least one Descriptor related to magic or a monstrous characteristic. Saint George regenerates Fervor Tokens equal to the number of Hunters at the beginning of each Scenario."}],"conditions":[],"agenda":["Hunt down and eliminate the Hunters who have proven themselves villains","Protect the Church and humanity from corrupted Order agents","Bring justice to those who abuse their power","Prevent more innocents from being harmed by these monsters"],"notes":"Saint George as OPPONENT is a persistent antagonist who appears throughout the campaign. The transition should be dramatic: public confrontation, evidence revealed, one chance to surrender, then summons Paladins (number = Hunters). During Witch Hunt: appears at worst moments, turns allies against Hunters, disrupts plans. Can still be redeemed by accumulating Judgment Tokens (twice number of Hunters) through good deeds. Brings unique Paladins equal to Hunter number (roll 1d6 to determine which). Voice: Harsh and accusatory, filled with righteous fury. Mannerisms: Points accusingly, quotes scripture, unwavering conviction."},"_id":"8f511750f1e0a0c8"}